  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nFoundryup\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nNone\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nNot sure if we can call it a bug, more like an doc issue\r\n\r\nI noticed that on https://getfoundry.sh/ it says that on windows you should build from source\r\n\r\nBut it seems to be working fine with binary too.\r\n\r\nit seems to only require bash (which user can get with https://gitforwindows.org/) and windows c++ build tools that they can get by installing visual studio community edition + Desktop C++ Development workload or by installing nodejs using the option to install the build tools \r\n\r\nSee some doc here :\r\n\r\n- with nodejs :  https://github.com/wighawag/template-foundry#windows \r\n- with visual studio community edition: https://github.com/wighawag/template-foundry/tree/bash#windows",
